Local soccer talent has been showcased in Soweto. SOWETO - For 17 years now, the Discovery Walter Sisulu Soccer Challenge draws thousands of fans into the heart of Soweto to see teams battle it out for the number one title. Among the crowds are scouts from professional football teams hoping to spot raw and promising talent. Every year, 92 teams divided into the under 17-division, the women’s division and first division teams enter to battle for the title. One well-known coach believes the tournament has had much success over the years. “The impact of the tournament is high and while it takes people away from the streets, it also gives players an opportunity to show talent to the world,” said Orlando Pirates assistant coach Rulani Mokoena. Tournaments like these have launched many a career.